w to adulthood, married, and mostly had large families — over 2,000 descendants are recorded. The Ingersoll-Yale lineage was one of the founding strata of Lee, Massachusetts; the marble from David's farm quarry helped build the U.S. Capitol."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"Two thousand descendants and counting","body":"The thirteen children she raised at Lee all married and “mostly had large families” — over two thousand descendants recorded by the 1926 Ingersoll genealogy, among them the founders of the Ingersoll Dollar Watch. Her widowed mother, a daughter of Jonathan Edwards, lived out years under her roof."}],"slug":"sarah-parsons-1760"}},"burialCemetery":null,"institutionsById":{},"crossConnections":[]}